HEADWORD: Lælaps
<hw>L⟦ae⟧"laps</hw> <pr>(l⟦emac⟧"l⟦acr⟧ps)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>lai^laps</grk> a dark, furious storm.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>A genus of huge, carnivorous, dinosaurian
reptiles from the Cretaceous formation of the United States. They had
very large hind legs and tail, and are supposed to have been bipedal.
Some of the species were about eighteen feet high.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

